A vintage-style illustration depicting two massive, ornate mechanical mail sorting machines from different eras facing each other across a vast warehouse floor. One machine is sleek and copper-toned with elegant clockwork gears visible through glass panels, while the other is bulkier with exposed iron pipes and steam vents. Between them, hundreds of paper envelopes and documents float mid-air in a chaotic swirl, some getting caught in the gears, others piling up on the floor. Workers in period-appropriate attire (waistcoats, rolled sleeves) scramble with wheelbarrows trying to manage the overflow. The lighting is warm amber from hanging industrial lamps, casting long shadows. The mood conveys the overwhelming complexity and friction of transitioning between incompatible systems, with a sense of organized chaos and endless labor.
